      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for hemolysis QoI at all five operating points with GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "GCI was computed at three of five operating points. At the high-speed, low-flow condition, GCI reached 11.2%, exceeding the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation was applied but asymptotic range was not confirmed. Achieved level 3 falls short of required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope within specified tolerances for flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid temperature.",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental data were collected at 37°C with bovine blood; COU specifies human blood at physiological temperature. Viscosity and red cell fragility differences introduce systematic bias not corrected in the comparison. Temperature tolerance was within bounds but blood analog equivalence is undemonstrated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., normalized RMS error) must be below 10% for hemolysis index across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error of 18.4% was observed across five operating points. Systematic over-prediction at high-speed conditions suggests model form error in the power-law hemolysis damage model. Achieved level 2 reflects inadequate agreement for Class III device acceptance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
